Bug Report Example (From Mozilla Bugzilla)

Bug ID: 1806079
Title: “Firefox crashes when switching tabs rapidly”
Product: Firefox
Component: Tabbed Browser
Status: NEW
Severity: Major
Reported by: janus@mozilla.org

Description:
When switching between tabs very quickly (Ctrl+Tab) Firefox crashes unexpectedly.
Crash reports show signatures related to nsWindow::DispatchEvent.

Steps to Reproduce:

Open 10+ tabs.

Hold down Ctrl+Tab for continuous tab switching.

Browser crashes after ~5–10 seconds.

Expected Result:
Browser should switch between tabs without crashing.

Actual Result:
Firefox crashes and restarts with crash reporter.
